The paper deals with computing approximate equilibria in two-player zero-sum extensive-form games with imperfect information, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves direct policy optimization, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses convergence rates and asymptotic behavior, which are topics in numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with sequential decision-making and adversarial settings, which are topics in control theory and systems (cs.SY).
